### ============================================================
# SteamTracker — HTTP Client Requests
# ============================================================
# Requires VS Code extension: "HTTP Client" by Huachao Mao (humao.rest-client)
# Prerequisites: devcontainer running with db & rabbitmq services.
# ============================================================

### --- Steam External API — Fetch price for a game ---
# Fetches price overview from the Steam Store API.
# Replace <APP_ID> with a real Steam App ID, e.g. 730 (CS2) or 570 (Dota 2).
GET https://store.steampowered.com/api/appdetails?appids=<APP_ID>&filters=price_overview&cc=de&l=german

### Example: CS2 free
GET https://store.steampowered.com/api/appdetails?appids=730&filters=price_overview&cc=de&l=german

### Example: Grand Theft Auto V (no longer available)
GET https://store.steampowered.com/api/appdetails?appids=362003&filters=price_overview&cc=de&l=german

### --- SteamTracker Internal API (WishlistApi on port 5186) ---
# The SteamTracker API runs inside the WishlistApi service on port 5186.
# Set X-Internal-UserId header for internal callers.

### Create an alert rule for a game
# POST /api/games/{appId}/alert?thresholdAmount=<amount>&currency=<currency>
# Requires: X-Internal-UserId header
POST http://localhost:5186/api/games/730/alert?thresholdAmount=20.00&currency=EUR
X-Internal-UserId: test-user-1

### Create an alert rule for another game
POST http://localhost:5186/api/games/570/alert?thresholdAmount=5.00&currency=EUR
X-Internal-UserId: test-user-1

### Delete an alert rule
# DELETE /api/alert/{alertRuleId}
# Replace <ALERT_RULE_ID> with a real GUID from your database.
DELETE http://localhost:5186/api/alert/<ALERT_RULE_ID>
X-Internal-UserId: test-user-1
